Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Picture: City of Tshwane) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; A Tshwane metro police officer was arrested for allegedly soliciting a bribe from an undercover officer on the Moloto road on Saturday, the Road Traffic Management Corporation said. &nbsp;The man allegedly asked for a R100 bribe from an undercover officer monitoring the conduct of his colleagues, spokesperson Simon Zwane said.It was part of an operation by the RTMC's national anti-corruption unit. The unit was at work countrywide to ensure that officers and motorists obeyed the law.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.